reviews.text: Was here to celebrate a special day and the vibe we expected was present. Outdoor lakeview patio with cozy lighting and they were cool with our tiny dog.  Great service, both waitresses service our group were awesome. Available, informative and positive. They also provided good portions of complimentary.  Decent collection of drinks. Would recommend Gyro platter and shrimp appetizer.

Great atmosphere, view, and location.
Prime 7 has the feel of being Up North from the log cabin feel decor to wall length window overlooking Cooley Lake. Staff and owner are so welcoming (just the way you'd feel Up North).
Aside from the spectacular views inside and out, it is a great place to catch any sort of sporting event on their many tvs (it was fun watching Kentucky Derby with everyone there), as well as live entertainment on a Saturday evening.
Their menu has great options, and everything coming out of the kitchen looks great (personally recommend chicken stir fry).
I perform throughout Michigan, so I have the benefit of experiencing different places, and I couldn't speak highly enough of Prime 7.

My bestie and I had dinner on the patio yesterday and it was a wonderful relaxing meal. Our salads were fresh, crisp and delicious, the atmosphere was beautiful with the lake across the street, and our server, Josie, took excellent care of us and she was so sweet! I‚Äôll definitely be back again soon as we live so close!

Love the steak and your fresh daily salads and soups. Very attentive staff and pleasant atmosphere looking over the Cooley lake. Prime 7 has definitely stepped up its service and menu options at very decent price. The new owner has done an amazing job with renovation of the patio and the old carpet area. Appreciate Lexi our waitress such an amazing girl pleasant to serve us. And the new owner Franco always shaking hands and making sure we are satisfied. Definitely recommend this place and will be back for more.

GREAT local spot - sports bar and restaurant, dining area for larger groups and private rooms as well, with a cozy feel and warm wooden lodge decor inside. Love the atmosphere.

The service and food is excellent - friendly servers, A+ meal offerings (comfort foods, classic dishes, and lighter options as well), solid presentation, I'm always happy after I leave Prime 7.

The patio and view from the front of the restaurant overlooks Cooley Lake. The staff and management are genuinely welcoming and friendly, and it's clear they have a good crew that gets on well as a team.

Thanks for the delicious meal, kind service, and pleasant atmosphere. Looking forward to coming back with friends for Karaoke on a Tuesday, and watching the Lions inevitably win the Superbowl soon üòâ
